WEBVTT

00:04:28.907 --> 00:04:33.146
Or that in that same period,
brave men -- knights --

00:04:33.170 --> 00:04:36.459
commonly fainted out of dismay?

00:04:37.474 --> 00:04:38.716
What if I was to tell you

00:04:38.740 --> 00:04:41.503
that some early Christians
who lived in the desert

00:04:41.527 --> 00:04:45.415
believed that flying demons
who mainly came out at lunchtime

00:04:45.439 --> 00:04:50.301
could infect them with an emotion
they called "accidie,"

00:04:50.325 --> 00:04:52.919
a kind of lethargy
that was sometimes so intense

00:04:52.943 --> 00:04:54.432
it could even kill them?

00:04:55.234 --> 00:04:59.370
Or that boredom,
as we know and love it today,

00:04:59.394 --> 00:05:02.421
was first really only felt
by the Victorians,